<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">&gt;
<step><![CDATA[soak cannellini beans overnight, then change water and cook with a pinch of bicarbonate 10 mins high heat and 40 mins medium low]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[sautÃ© the onions in olive oil at medium-high heat until caramelized, like hot dog onions, 10m. Add rosemary or other herbs if using]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Meanwhile cook the pasta as normal]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[if using bacon / sausage, add and saute another 3 mins, and add chilli powder for last 30 secs. Otherwise add chopped chilies 3m]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[sweat with white wine if using, 2 mins then add a third of the beans and mash with a fork, then add the remaining beans and the passata if using]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[keep cooking adding a bit of pasta water every so often to keep liquid, or stock if using]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[when the pasta is ready season sauce with salt and pepper and add pasta to it. Sprinkle teared basil leaves on it and serve]]></step>
&gt;</directions>
